# === Negations: explicitly keep these committed ===
# Project-level Claude guide.
!CLAUDE.md
# Parity fixtures generated from reference NumPy SWAMPE.
!unit_tests/fixtures/*.npz
# JOSS paper figures + logo. The paper is LaTeX (paper.tex is canonical; no .md).
# Figure 1 (parity) needs the external reference SWAMPE to regenerate, so the
# rendered figures are committed; the regenerable .npz data and the .pdf are not.
!paper/*.png
